# .trivyignore — accepted-risk exceptions for the Trivy security gate.
#
# The pipeline FAILS the build on any fixable HIGH/CRITICAL (see
# .github/workflows/build-and-push.yml). Prefer FIXING vulnerabilities
# (bump the dependency / base image). Only add a CVE here when it is genuinely
# not exploitable in this app AND cannot yet be upgraded — every entry is a
# conscious, reviewed exception, not a way to silence the scanner.
#
# Rules for adding an entry (keep the gate meaningful):
#   1. One CVE ID per line.
#   2. A comment above it: why it's not exploitable + owner + date.
#   3. An expiry so it can't live forever: `CVE-XXXX-YYYY exp:2026-12-31`.
#   4. Re-evaluate on every dependency bump; delete once a fix is shipped.
#
# There are currently NO active exceptions — everything flagged so far was
# fixed by upgrading (starlette 1.3.1, path-to-regexp 0.1.13). The examples
# below are COMMENTED OUT and ignore nothing.
#
# ---- EXAMPLE (do not uncomment unless it truly applies) --------------------
# Starlette StaticFiles SSRF — not exploitable here: this API never mounts
# StaticFiles. Accepted by <me> on 2026-07-01, revisit by year end.
# (Already moot — we upgraded to starlette 1.3.1 which fixes it.)
# CVE-2026-48818 exp:2026-12-31
#
# Example of a base-image CVE with no fix available yet:
# CVE-2025-00000 exp:2026-09-30
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
